fix(training): make eligible feature snapshots idempotent

- Add partial unique index `idx_feature_snapshots_unique_eligible` on
  (symbol, interval, candle_open_time, feature_schema_hash) WHERE training_eligible=true
  in both initial schema creation and migration path
- Update `record_feature_snapshot()` to use ON CONFLICT ... WHERE training_eligible = true
  DO UPDATE to upsert feature_names/feature_values and return existing snapshot_id
- Extend audit_repair_training_data.py to detect and invalidate duplicate snapshots
  (same symbol, interval, candle_open_time, feature_schema_hash) by marking them
  training_eligible=false with invalid_reason='duplicate_snapshot_same_candle'
- Keeps the first (oldest) snapshot per group as eligible, invalidates extras
- No dead scaffold files (snapshot_idempotency.py, snapshot_write_idempotency.py) exist